snippet.textDisplay: The comfort transmission setting in the RS-5 is horrible, it takes an eternity for the car to just roll off from a stop light let alone race from a rolling start. Personally, I always have the transmission set in dynamic and the suspension in comfort... although you have to remember to pull back on the paddle each time you start or it will automatically put the transmission in comfort even if you have it set in to dynamic mode when you turn the car off. The car is great, but for canyon carving and back road driving I'd still take the Porsche as the steering feel and feedback is much better in the 911.
snippet.textOriginal: The comfort transmission setting in the RS-5 is horrible, it takes an eternity for the car to just roll off from a stop light let alone race from a rolling start. Personally, I always have the transmission set in dynamic and the suspension in comfort... although you have to remember to pull back on the paddle each time you start or it will automatically put the transmission in comfort even if you have it set in to dynamic mode when you turn the car off. The car is great, but for canyon carving and back road driving I'd still take the Porsche as the steering feel and feedback is much better in the 911.
